<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Panteroo on 05-17-2002 12:25 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well...

I've done this a couple times and, IMHO, unless your single group is all in NToV + Primal your best bet would be to bring a couple groups.

Just a few observations from my perspective. Bards are amazingly effective in this cycle. Mana free mez's, ae mana, mana free charms, stacking haste... Unless your VERY good your likely going to fall behind during some point in the 3rd wave between the double spawns and room repops, and bards help alot with keeping multiples mezzed/charmed. Melee damage is your friend over the long haul. If I were to put together an "optimal" 2 non-uber groups to do this I would opt to have (assuming all 55+ with most closer to 60):

1 Warrior
1 SK
2 Epic Monks
2 Epic Rogues
2 Clerics
1 Enchanter
1 Bard
1 Wiz
1 Shaman

We always have somebody (usually me) with a second char on a second PC to be the shackle bait. I like having a druid shackled because I can assist heal, nuke, and provide a damage shield and never have to press more than 2 hotkeys to do it. The high priest, named or not, isn't that difficult but he has alot of hitpoints and we invariably make it tougher by always seeming to get a CH'ing room respawn at the wrong time.

I imagine that a single group could do it if they were very well equipped and very coordinated... but that is far beyond my guilds capabilities... if your gimp and you know it clap your hands *clap* *clap*  :)



------------------
[URL=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12024]Panteroo Mcgillakudy[/URL]
High Priest of Fennin Ro</TEXTAREA>
